## Change Request #1 — Improved Series Detection

### Current algorithm (in `isSeriesGroup`, grouper.go lines 466-506):
- Requires all filenames to share the same prefix
- Requires numeric suffixes to be **strictly consecutive** (gap ≤ 1)
- Only checks filenames, ignores EXIF timestamps and camera info
- Only activates on groups with confidence ≥ 95%

### New algorithm — Two independent criteria (either triggers "series"):

**Criterion A — Filename sequential (relaxed):**
- Same filename prefix (case-insensitive)
- Numeric suffixes sorted: max gap ≤ 5 (not 1)
- This catches IMG_4446, IMG_4448, IMG_4450, IMG_4451

**Criterion B — Time+Camera proximity (new):**
- All files have the same EXIF camera make+model
- All files have EXIF DateTimeOriginal within 60 seconds of each other
- This catches bursts where filenames don't follow a pattern

Either criterion A OR B triggers "series" classification.

